TITLE: Validating SQL Query with If-Else Node
DESCRIPTION: This snippet checks if the generated SQL query is valid by ensuring it contains 'SELECT' and 'WHERE' clauses.
SOURCE: https://github.com/flowiseai/flowisedocs/blob/main/en/use-cases/sql-qna.md#2025-04-18_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const sqlQuery = $sqlQuery.trim();

const regex = /SELECT\s.*?(?:\n|$)/gi;

// Extracting the SQL part
const matches = sqlQuery.match(regex);
const cleanSql = matches ? matches[0].trim() : "";

if (cleanSql.includes("SELECT") && cleanSql.includes("WHERE")) {
    return cleanSql;
}
```

